<h1><u><strong>Customer advises regarding the Coronavirus</strong></u><br />
Last update 25/09/20</h1>
<p>As the news is dominated by the coronavirus, we wanted to let you know that we are vigilantly implementing improved protocols to ensure your safety, as well as the flexibility of your Transportation Service.</p>
<p>The safety of our customers and our teams is of utmost importance to us. We are closely following news, advice and warnings from the World Health Organization regarding the spread of the Coronavirus. Our goal is to meet your every need while ensuring your safety and that of our employees.</p>
<h2>Are all your Grewal Transport service agencies in India open?</h2>
<p><br />
In accordance with government directives and to support the collective effort to fight the Covid-19 pandemic, we are forced to close some of our branches. Our booking engine is updated in real-time with information about the opening times and schedules of our agencies.</p>
<h3>Mandatory mask-wearing</h3>
<p><br />
In accordance with government directives, the wearing of masks for the general public is made compulsory in all our agencies, in addition to barrier gestures, as of July 01, 2020. We reserve the right to refuse access to our agencies to all people not wearing masks</p>
<h4>How can I contact you regarding a new or existing reservation?</h4>
<p><br />
In light of global efforts to limit the spread of the coronavirus, the latest government measures may have an impact on the handling of calls in our Transport Offices. You can make a booking on our site.</p>
<p>If you wish to cancel a Booking, please note that the cancellation fee will not be charged for booking starting before December 15, 2020. To modify or cancel an existing reservation, you can manage your Booking on this site.</p>
<p>All our teams thank you for your understanding and your patience.<br />
&nbsp;</p>

